<article>
    <h1>Panel&#x2019;s call to pro&#xAD;tect works gen&#xAD;er&#xAD;ated by com&#xAD;put&#xAD;ers</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200803/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-03"><time>2020-08-03</time></a>
        - <span>HOME</span>
        - <span role="byline">K. C. Vi&#xAD;jayan</span>
    </section>

    <p>A law re­form team of the Sin­ga­pore Academy of Law (SAL) has called for amend­ments to copy­right law to pro­tect “com­put­er­gen­er­ated works” that have no hu­man au­thor.</p>
    <p>It also sug­gests more clar­ity on how ex­ist­ing “com­pi­la­tion rights” ap­ply to elec­tronic data­bases.</p>
    <p>Th­ese are among the rec­om­men­da­tions in a re­port pub­lished last month by a sub-com­mit­tee on ro­bot­ics and ar­ti­fi­cial in­tel­li­gence co-chaired by Jus­tice Kan­nan Ramesh and Mr Charles Lim Aeng Cheng.</p>
    <p>The re­port comes at a time when the enor­mous growth in the gen­er­a­tion and col­lec­tion of per­sonal and non-per­sonal dig­i­tal data has driven the cre­ation of large datasets and data­bases to ag­gre­gate and ar­range that data.</p>
    <p>“Those datasets and data­bases are the ‘stock feed’ on which AI (ar­ti­fi­cial in­tel­li­gence) sys­tems – and ma­chine learn­ing AI sys­tems in par­tic­u­lar – rely.</p>
    <p>“As such, the le­gal and pol­icy land­scape gov­ern­ing those data­bases is of cru­cial im­por­tance,” says the re­port.</p>
    <p>It points out such big data data­bases can drive sig­nif­i­cant so­ci­etal ben­e­fits, es­pe­cially for third par­ties to com­bine with other datasets in their pos­ses­sion to de­rive higher qual­ity data anal­y­sis.</p>
    <p>Not­ing the cur­rent patent and copy­right regime and other mech­a­nisms in place, the re­port rec­om­mends “that copy­right pro­tec­tion of com­puter-gen­er­ated works be recog­nised through leg­isla­tive amend­ments modelled on equiv­a­lent UK copy­right laws, with guid­ance pro­vided in the in­terim on when com­puter-gen­er­ated works en­joy copy­right pro­tec­tion”.</p>
    <p>The full re­port can be found at https://www.sal.org.sg/ Re­sources-Tools/LawRe­form/Robotic­s_AI_Series#DataRe­port</p>


</article>

